author: Dailymail.Com Reporter
title: Brady and Gisele arrive back in Boston after Super Bowl | Daily Mail Online
text: Tom Brady and Gisele arrive back in Boston after historic Super Bowl victory as his Patriots coach sends a not-so-subtle message to NFL commissioner who suspended the quarterback Patriots star Tom Brady and his wife Gisele Bundchen arrived in Boston Monday The pair were seen getting of a jet with their children, Vivian and Benjamin Brady's sister, Nancy, and her husband Steve Bonelli, also traveled with them The family arrived back in Boston following Brady's historic Super Bowl victory Meanwhile, defense coordinator, Matt Patricia wore shirt with Goodell as clown Tension between Patriots and NFL commissioner came about after Deflategate Shirt seemed to signify team's revenge after Goodell penalized them in 2015 Goodell fined Patriots $1 million and suspended Tom Brady for first four games Star quarterback now has five championships and four Super Bowl MVPs Patriots claimed win over Atlanta Falcons in first overtime in Super Bowl history New England battled back from a 25-point deficit to win 34-28 in Super Bowl LI Published: 01:06 GMT, 7 February 2017 | Updated: 04:23 GMT, 7 February 2017 573 shares
